{"id":"ev_d71cc24b1b914125","runId":"run_231","type":"delegation","at":1782325548720,"data":{"workItemId":"wi_80bfa603780d4ae4","atom":0,"task":"Adopt a minimal, restrained ESLint 9 flat config in CoCoder's own engine repo (ticket 0048). This atom: land the config + lint script + reach a HONEST green. CI-gate wiring, docs, and ticket close are a SEPARATE later atom — do NOT touch .github/workflows/ci.yml, the `test` script, the ticket file, or docs in this atom.\n\nWHAT TO DO:\n1. Install pinned dev deps at the repo root with pnpm: `eslint@^9` and `@typescript-eslint`'s flat-config bits (`typescript-eslint@^8` meta-package is the simplest, or `@typescript-eslint/parser@^8` + `@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin@^8`). Pin to the REAL versions pnpm actually installs (read them back from package.json after install — no guessed pins). Mirror CoBuilder's eslint 9.x + @typescript-eslint 8.x baseline.\n2. Create `eslint.config.mjs` at the repo root. Keep it RESTRAINED and well-commented (mirror the spirit of CoBuilder/infrastructure/eslint.config.mjs). Target `packages/*/src/**/*.ts` and `scripts/**/*.mjs`. Ignore `**/node_modules/**`, `**/dist/**`, and `packages/ui/**` (ui is already excluded from typecheck — exclude it here too to avoid scope creep; note that in a comment).\n   Enable ONLY the high-value class the ticket names — the bugs tsc+vitest miss — and nothing noisy:\n     - Floating/unhandled promises + forgotten await: `@typescript-eslint/no-floating-promises`, `@typescript-eslint/no-misused-promises` (these are TYPE-AWARE — set `languageOptions.parserOptions.projectService: true` or point `project` at the tsconfig so they work).\n     - Dangerous eval family: `no-eval`, `no-implied-eval`, `no-new-func`.\n     - Leftover debug: `no-console` (error). If a few legitimate console sites exist (e.g. CLI output), allow them narrowly via `{ allow: ['warn','error'] }` OR per-file disable comments — do NOT blanket-disable the rule.\n     - Dead/unused code: `@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars` (with the standard `argsIgnorePattern: '^_'` escape hatch).\n   Do NOT add stylistic/formatting rules or a large recommended preset that creates noise. This is a safety net, not a style police.\n3. Add a `lint` script to root package.json: `\"lint\": \"eslint .\"` (or scoped equivalent).\n4. Run `pnpm lint` and reach GREEN HONESTLY. Fix real violations at the root cause. If a specific violation is genuinely out of scope to fix in this atom, scope it out DELIBERATELY and VISIBLY (a targeted file/line eslint-disable WITH a one-line justification comment, or a narrow `files`/`ignores` carve-out with a comment) — never weaken a rule to a tautology or blanket-disable to fake green. Keep a short list of exactly what you fixed vs. what you deliberately scoped out, and why.\n\nMUST NOT BREAK: `pnpm typecheck` and `pnpm test` must still pass. Do not modify product behavior to satisfy a lint rule — if a rule flags real code, fix the actual defect (e.g. add the missing await) or scope it out visibly; do not silently change semantics.\n\nEVIDENCE TO REPORT: the installed versions (from package.json), the full `eslint.config.mjs`, the `pnpm lint` output showing 0 errors, and `pnpm typecheck` still green. List every deliberate scope-out (file + rule + one-line reason)."}}
